            "text": "While you might at first just notice the three-inch chop at the top, the customizations for this car are literally everywhere. It rides lower thanks to a set of new springs. Then the body has a different look with the combination of a nosed hood with rounded corners, shaved door handles and emblems, decked trunk lid, restyled bumpers, 1953 Buick side trim, molded grille shell with 1952 DeSoto grille and additional teeth, flush-fit skirts, and 1954 Mercury taillights. This really is quite the car to sit back and admire.",
